Others: De'Aaron Fox posted another strong scoring outing just one day after finding his way to a franchise-record 60-point stat line.
Fox finished with 49 points, three rebounds, and nine assists in an effort that was done without Domantas Sabonis, Malik Monk, and DeMar DeRozan.
Utah Jazz head coach Will Hardy praised De'Aaron Fox's performance, noting his difficulty to keep in front and his effectiveness in the mid-range.
